<TITLE> Mahmudur sues home ministry over exit bar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 1 (bdnews24.com)  Former energy adviser and acting editor of Amar Desh Mahmudur Rahman has filed a case against the home ministry and two senior government officials claiming Tk 42 crore in damages. Rahman, who is also vice chairman of Artisan Ceramics Limited, claims that on Feb 9 the home ministry, its secretary Abdus Sobhan Sikder and the officer in charge of the immigration police wing at Shahjalal International Airport Azizur Rahman illegally barred him from leaving the country. As a result, he says, he was prevented from attending a five-day trade fair in German losing him significant business opportunities. Imrul Qayes of Dhaka's 1st district Judge's Court set Apr 15 as the date for him to submit court fees. 
